---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Jordan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/jordan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Egypt for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/egypt' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
  { title: 'Israel for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/israel' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'jordanFit', header: 'Jordan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD 260-370/mo', jordanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD 305-435/mo', jordanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD 240-345/mo', jordanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD 220-315/mo', jordanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Jordanian Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'JOD 50-150/mo', jordanFit: 'Basic Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'JOD 240-370', annual: 'JOD 2,880-4,440' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'JOD 330-495', annual: 'JOD 3,960-5,940' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'JOD 445-665', annual: 'JOD 5,340-7,980' },
  { category: 'Jordanian Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'JOD 25-70/visit' },
  { category: 'Jordanian Public', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: 'Limited access' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jordan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Jordan. Petra wonder, Dead Sea wellness, medical tourism hub, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jordan"
  subheadline="Jordan offers Petra ancient wonder, Dead Sea wellness, excellent medical tourism hospitals, and moderate living costs—a stable Middle Eastern retirement option."
  heroImage="/images/countries/jordan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Jordan</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan offers stability in a turbulent region—Petra ancient wonder, Dead Sea wellness, excellent hospitals, and warm hospitality. Medical tourism is a major industry with JCI-accredited hospitals. The country welcomes foreigners and has established expat communities.
  </p>

  <p>
    Amman provides capital living with best healthcare. Dead Sea area offers wellness retreats and therapeutic benefits. Aqaba provides Red Sea access. Petra is iconic but remote. The country is small and accessible, with English widely spoken.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; JCI-accredited hospitals</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> JOD 700-1,500/month (~$1,000-2,100); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean/semi-arid; hot summers</li>
      <li><strong>Stability:</strong> Most stable country in the region</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Welcoming; historic; medical tourism hub</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Jordan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan has excellent healthcare—major medical tourism destination. Jordan Hospital, Abdali Hospital, King Hussein Cancer Center are JCI-accredited. Many doctors US/UK trained. Prices are 30-50% below Western rates with comparable quality.
  </p>

  <p>
    Medical tourism brings patients from across Middle East and beyond. Cardiac, orthopedic, oncology, and cosmetic procedures are specialties. International insurance is recommended for best hospital access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Tourism Leader</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Jordan is the Middle East leading medical tourism destination. JCI-accredited hospitals, US-trained doctors, and competitive pricing attract regional and international patients. Quality healthcare is a key advantage for retirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan offers straightforward options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Property investment of JOD 50,000+ (~$70,000) or bank deposit qualifies for residence. Renewable permit with right to live and work.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Tourist visa easily extended. Many retirees use extended tourist stays while exploring formal residence options.
  </p>

  <h3>Income-Based Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Demonstrating income and local ties can support residence applications through Ministry of Interior.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Jordan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Private coverage for best hospital access</li>
    <li><strong>Medical tourism:</strong> Jordan hospitals accept most international insurance</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> Consider including nearby countries</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Jordan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is recommended for access to JCI-accredited hospitals. Jordan healthcare is excellent and affordable. Coverage ensures access to best facilities and regional evacuation if ever needed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Jordan, international coverage with regional access works well:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Jordan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good MENA network, covers JCI hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Middle East expertise, regional knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive regional pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well for Jordan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Jordan are moderate given excellent healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Jordanian private care is affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations JOD 25-50; affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional coverage:</strong> MENA focused rather than worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Dead Sea wellness:</strong> Therapeutic benefits included in lifestyle</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American History Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Fascinated by Petra and biblical sites.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Investor residence via property. Cigna Global with US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~JOD 300/month (~$420). Ancient wonders; excellent healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Wellness Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension £2,400/month. Seeking Dead Sea therapeutic benefits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Based near Dead Sea; Amman for hospitals.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~JOD 750/month combined (~£850). Wellness lifestyle; quality healthcare.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Palestinian Diaspora, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Jordanian-American dual citizen. $1,800/month pension. Returning to region.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Now Health regional coverage. Uses Jordan Hospital network.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~JOD 250/month (~$350). Near family; excellent value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Jordan safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—most stable country in the region. Monarchy provides stability. Security is well-managed. Border areas with Syria should be avoided. Main cities and tourist areas are safe. Jordan has long welcomed Western visitors and expats.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Jordanian healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—Jordan is Middle East medical tourism leader. JCI-accredited hospitals, US/UK trained doctors, modern equipment. King Hussein Cancer Center is regionally renowned. Quality rivals developed countries at lower cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the Dead Sea benefits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Therapeutic—Dead Sea minerals and low altitude (400m below sea level) provide health benefits. Psoriasis, arthritis, and respiratory conditions improve. Medical tourism packages combine treatment with wellness stays. Unique health advantage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get by with English?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—English is widely spoken. Healthcare professionals, business, and tourism operate in English. Arabic helps for daily life but isn't essential. Jordan is one of the easier Arab countries for English speakers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with MENA coverage for Jordan.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Jordanian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
